title: 820-2936 shorted PCH?
message:
Have a 820-2936 that had liquid damage and worked for a short bit after replacing everything affected by the spill but board died again during testing.

Checked power rails and found a short on PPV_SUS. I removed everything on that line excep tPCH but still have short. Does this confirm PCH needs to be replaced?

title: 820-2936 shorted PCH?
message:
Have a 820-2936 that had liquid damage and worked for a short bit after replacing everything affected by the spill but board died again during testing.

Checked power rails and found a short on PP5V_SUS. I removed everything on that line except PCH but still have short. Does this confirm PCH needs to be replaced?

title: 820-2936 shorted PCH?
message:
Is that short lower, or higher than 10 ohms?
Higher value points to PCH, or C2438.
If PP5V_SUS_PCH_V5REFSUS shows lower value than PP5V_SUS (when C2438 removed), try heating PCH with good flux.
